  <question type="stack">
    <name>
      <text>Parabola - line intersection (from FAC: 3.2.1 parabola - line intersection, from graph)</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p><b>(a)</b> Find the equation of the parabola shown in the diagram.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"></p>
<div style="margin-left:4em;margin-right:auto;">[[jsxgraph width='200px' height='200px']] JXG.Options.axis.ticks.majorHeight = 60; JXG.Options.axis.ticks.insertTicks = false; JXG.Options.axis.ticks.ticksDistance = 50; JXG.Options.text.fontSize = 16; var board = JXG.JSXGraph.initBoard(divid, {boundingbox:
    {#BB#}, axis: true, showCopyright: false, showNavigation:false}); var f = board.jc.snippet('{#quad#}', true, 'x', true); board.create('functiongraph', [f,{#BB[1]#},{#BB[3]#}],{strokeColor:'#003399',strokeWidth:2}); var g = board.jc.snippet('{#line#}',
    true, 'x', true); board.create('functiongraph', [g,{#BB[1]#},{#BB[3]#}],{strokeColor:'#003399',strokeWidth:2}); var p = board.create('point',{#P#}, {name:'({#P[1]#},{#P[2]#})',size:3,fixed:true,strokeColor:'#003399',fillColor:'#003399',label:{anchorX:'middle',offset:
    [0, 20]}}); var c = board.create('point',{#C#}, {name:'({#C[1]#},{#C[2]#})',size:3,fixed:true,strokeColor:'#003399',fillColor:'#003399',label:{anchorX:'right',anchorY:'top',offset: [0, -5]}}); [[/jsxgraph]]
</div>
<p></p>
    &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; \(y=\) [[input:ans1]][[validation:ans1]][[feedback:prt1]]
<p></p>

    <b>(b) </b>Find the points of intersection of this parabola with the line \( y = {@line@} \). &nbsp; <br>
<p></p>
&nbsp; &nbsp; Points of intersection: [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]][[feedback:prt2]]
<p></p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="html">
      <text><![CDATA[<p><b>(a) </b>The parabola has its turning point at \(({@P[1]@},{@P[2]@})\) so its equation will be of the form \(y={@k*(x-P[1])^2+P[2]@}\).</p><p>Since the parabola passes through&nbsp;\(({@C[1]@},{@C[2]@})\) we have \( {@C[2]@}={@ev(k*(x-P[1])^2+P[2],x=C[1])@} \) thus \(k={@(C[2]-P[2])/(C[1]-P[1])^2@}\).</p><p>So the parabola has equation \(y={@ta1@}\).</p><p><b>(b) </b>We need to find the points of intersection of \( y = {@quad@}\) and \( y = {@line@} \), so we solve:</p><p>\[\begin{align*} {@quad@} &amp;= {@line@} \\ {@quad-line@} &amp;= 0 \\ {@factor(quad-line)@} &amp;=0\end{align*} \]</p><p>So the solutions are \(x_1={@a@}\), \(x_2={@b@}\).</p><p>For \( x_1 = {@a@}, \quad y_1 = {@y_a@} \).</p><p>For \( x_2 = {@b@}, \quad y_2 = {@y_b@} \).<br></p><p>So, the intersection points are {@ta2@}.</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
